  "details": "Grunt is the JavaScript task runner. Why use a task runner? In one word: automation. The less work you have to do when performing repetitive tasks like minification, compilation, unit testing, linting, etc, the easier your job becomes. After you've configured it, a task runner can do most of that mundane work for you with basically zero effort.\r\n\r\nSecurity Fix(es):\nPath Traversal in GitHub repository gruntjs/grunt prior to 1.5.2.(CVE-2022-0436)",
